# Product Contract: <feature name>

User-facing contract for one feature. Maintained alongside the feature; reviewed against every change that touches it. PM reads to understand what the feature promises; agents read to know what must keep working.

One contract per user-facing feature. Backend-only changes (refactors, infra) do not need a contract — they touch existing contracts only if they change visible behavior.

---

## User value

